                                        whether by adding to or subtracting from the area thereof or
                                        otherwise;

enters or resides in a National Park otherwise than in the
                                        course of his duty as a public officer or as a person
                                        lawfully employed in the Park;

cuts, injures or sets fire to any vegetation in a National
                                        Park, or allows any fire lighted by himself or his servants
                                        to enter a National Park;

the conditions under, and the extent to, which any of the acts mentioned in subsection (2)
or subsection (3)
of section 13 may be lawfully performed and the fees to be paid in respect of such performance;

the registration may be effected in respect of the whole of
                                        the land of such owner or of such portion thereof as the
                                        owner may specify;

if the animal wounded is a dangerous animal, to a fine not
                                        exceeding ten thousand shillings or to imprisonment for a
                                        term not exceeding two years or to both;

(a) sell, buy, use or have in his possession any gin or
                                        similar trap having a jaw length of four inches or more, or
                                        any snare or similar contrivance made of wire;

any firearm capable of firing more than one missile as a
                                        result of one pressure of the trigger or of reloading itself
                                        without further action by the operator;

hunt any game animal during the period between seven o'clock
                                        in the evening and half-past five o'clock in the
                                        morning;

any animal or trophy in respect of which a breach of any of
                                        the provisions of this Act or the rules has been
                                        committed;

shall be subject to the payment of the prescribed fee, and
                                        different fees may be prescribed for different classes of
                                        dealers;

any licence, permit or other document required to be had or
                                        be kept by such person under the provisions of this Act or
                                        the rules;

where any apparently unlawful means of hunting cannot
                                        practicably be removed from its location it may forthwith be
                                        rendered inoperative;

specify the conditions subject to which any licence, permit
                                        or authorization may be granted or issued under this
                                        Act;

classify game licences and specify the animals which may be
                                        included in any game licence, and the numbers thereof which
                                        may be hunted under that licence;

prohibit the use of any specified type or calibre of weapon
                                        in the hunting of any specified type of game animal or game
                                        bird;

make provision for the manner and time in which applications for the award of compensation under section 62
may be made, for prescribing the level of such compensation and for the regulation of the proceedings of District Committees established under that section and the Appeal Tribunal established under section 65
and the manner and time within which appeals under section 65(3) may be made;
